segments.text: Hello again, Frank12Castle. I know it's been quite a long time since I've done one of these, but I was very busy, and you all probably saw movies over Christmas that you wanted to see anyway, so I'm back.
Anyway, I want to go see The Green Hornet, which of course stars Seth Rogen, who also helped write the movie. It was directed by Mike Gondry.
It stars other actors such as Jay Chow, Christoph Waltz, and Cameron Diaz.

The Green Hornet is a radio show, like The Lone Ranger, and The Green Hornet was essentially like Batman. He was a normal guy who used gadgets and his sidekick to help fight crime, usually the Nazis, but that's not what this movie was about.
The way The Green Hornet was done via Seth Rogen's point of view, it was a parody. The Green Hornet, his real name is Britt Reid, he doesn't know how to do much.
When he fights, he just brawls. He has no science behind it. In fact, most of the work is done by Kato. Kato fights for The Green Hornet.

He makes The Black Beauty, which is the car The Green Hornet uses. He makes gadgets for The Green Hornet, and he doesn't get that much recognition, but he helps out because he wants to fight for good.
The movie starts off as any superhero movie would. You have a character, you have the main character, who has a crisis happen in his life, and then he becomes a hero. That is what this movie is.
I thought the characters were well done. I loved how Seth Rogen played The Green Hornet, and I loved how Jay Chow played Kato. They did very good jobs.
Christoph Waltz plays the bad guy. He was the bad guy in Glorious Basterds. He just keeps doing that. The bad guy where he seems calm, but deep down he's an insane psychopath.
He plays that well. He's a good villain. He also has a really cool gun. It's like a desert eagle, but it has two barrels to it. It's pretty scary looking. I wouldn't want that pointed at me.

Cameron Diaz plays the love interest. She's a very, very, very bright journalist. Britt Reid hires her on her good looks, but he finds out there's actually a lot more to her than he initially thought.
He's always trying to get her to fall in love with him, but of course she doesn't want anything to do with him. Who would? Seth Rogen.
Anyway, I digress. Like I said, I thought the movie was great. The action they do have is really well done. They did a good job with the car. They did a good job with the fight scenes.
They had the Sherlock Holmes fight scenes where they slow down, they go through everything. I think if you're not a Seth Rogen fan, you definitely will not like this movie.
It has a lot of his humor in it. I thought it was funny, like I like Pineapple Express, and I like Knocked Up, and he was a four year old virgin. I don't think that matters, but I like that too.
So honestly, if you don't like Seth Rogen, you're not going to like this movie. I guess it's a family movie. There's not too much bad stuff that goes on in it.

But then again, I'm not a parent. There's some light cursing scenes, and the violence they do have isn't that bad. But yeah, if you wanted to bring your kids to go see it, I recommend it. It's not going to be detrimental to them.

I'm trying to think what else. I think I've hit upon everything. Honestly, I guess I'm a bit prejudiced because I like superheroes in all the superhero movies. I was very excited for this. This was like the major thing I wanted to see.

So yeah, I guess if I had to put a label on it. Good movie. A lot of action. We'll keep you entertained. Where you're not filled with action, there's comedy to help ease it along. It has a pretty good story, I think.
Well, I guess that's pretty much it. Honestly, you're either going to go see this movie because you've wanted to for a while, or you're not going to see it because you honestly could care less.
But don't believe everything that Rotten Tomatoes or the media says about it. If you really like superheroes, go see the movie. I guarantee you'll like it.
If I had to rate this movie at a 5, I'd give it a 4. But that's just me being me.
So I hope you liked my review. I hope to have another one soon. Please subscribe. And I guess that's it. I hope you all had a great holiday and I'm back.
